| Win McNamee/Getty Images White House Trump officials prepared to stonewall Democratic oversight demands Trump doesn’t plan to negotiate with Congress over investigations the way his predecessors did.
AdvertisementIt was just one example of the Trump White House’s unusually hostile — or in this case, non-existent — response to congressional investigators.
POLITICO contacted the 17 House committees that unsuccessfully requested records or witnesses from the Trump administration over the last two months.
Even by those standards, Trump officials are taking the fight to a level that Congressional and White House veterans call unprecedented.
Six administration officials refused to appear before five committees while two officials have refused to come in for interviews with two other committees, they say.